com.stormpath.sdk.factor.google

Interface GoogleAuthenticatorFactor<T extends GoogleAuthenticatorChallenge>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Auditable, Deletable, Factor<T>, Resource, Saveable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultGoogleAuthenticatorFactor

    public interface GoogleAuthenticatorFactor<T extends GoogleAuthenticatorChallenge>
extends Factor<T>
    A GoogleAuthenticatorFactor is a Factor that represents a two-step verification services using the Time-based One-time Password Algorithm (TOTP) and HMAC-based One-time Password Algorithm (HOTP), for authenticating users of mobile applications by Google.

    The TOTP algorithm determines the next valid code without the requirement for any communication between server and TOTP client.

    As such, the challenge can be created with the code at the same time: 

     GoogleAuthenticatorChallenge challenge = googleAuthenticatorFactor.createChallenge(code);
    Since:
    1.1.0
